literals: 'Either over the stove or in a microwavable bowl, melt the peanut butter and chocolate chips.'
'In a mixing bowl, add 3 cups of cereal.'
'Pour 1 cup of the chocolate mixture over the cereal.'
'Repeat this process with adding 3 more cups of cereal and the remaining chocolate mixture.'
'If there are pools of the chocolate mixture, add 1/4 cup of cereal at a time until all the chocolate mixture is used.'
'Place this in the fridge for maybe 15 minutes. You do not want it to harden because it makes the powdered sugar more difficult to stick.'
'Let the mixture come to room temperature.'
'Add 1 cup of powdered sugar and mix.'
'Chill in the fridge again for 15 minutes.'
'Add 1/4 cup of powdered sugar and mix. Repeat with the remaining powdered sugar.'
'Enjoy these sweet goodies while watching a movie or reading a book.'
'Store at room temperature in an airtight container.'
